      "content": "If the situation is tending toward heated or disruptive, focus on the confrontation and the intensity of the protest. Try \"Tensions Rise in Downtown Plaza as Reform Groups March,\" which suggests escalation without promising full-blown violence. Alternatively, \"Clashes Possible: Protests Intensify Near City Hall,\" offers a cautionary, on-the-ground feel. For a more direct tone reflecting heavy presence, \"Crowds Converge Amid High Police Presence Demanding Change.\"",
      "source": "target",
